    "body": "I use this `CappedCrowdsale` as a base contract. Then I call both base constructors:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontract MyCrowdSale is CappedCrowdsale {\r\n    function MyCrowdSale(uint256 _cap, uint256 _startTime, uint256 _endTime, uint256 _rate, address _wallet) CappedCrowdsale(_cap) Crowdsale(_startTime, _endTime, _rate, _wallet) {\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis approach seems a bit cleaner than passing constructor arguments through to the base constructor.",
